    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>,  p. 111, n. <citedRange>86</citedRange>, fig. 42</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.198</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>024200</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, p. <citedRange>204</citedRange> (date of the base)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>139</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65184"><name nymRef="#Ξεναρίστα">Ξεναρίστα</name> 
                            <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65483"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Πρατομήδης">Πρατομήδευς</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Xenarista fille de Pratomédès.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Xenarista daughter of Pratomedes.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Xenarista figlia di Pratomedes.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Oliverio (followed by Beschi and the Thorns) said that the base came from a necropolis, but the footprints on top are uncommon for a funerary use. 
                    It might rather be private honours.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
